Questions after the accident: Are hostesses illegal on buses?
The law is unknown, you can&#39;t walk on a long-distance bus
In connection with the tragic accident involving the Student Agency bus near the Italian city of Padova, the question arises as to whether the hostesses and passengers can move around the bus during the trip.
&quot;If we wanted to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of the stewardess is contrary to the road traffic law,&quot; says the spokesman for the Ministry of Transport, Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in which the twenty-two-year-old flight attendant died last week was evidently caused by the truck driver, except that the bus crossed the road.
The girl, unfortunately, was sitting next to the driver in the least safe place in the vehicle despite having two other places reserved.
However, the bus can have an accident or stop suddenly, and at the precise moment when the steward delivers coffee or newspapers.
What plays a role here is whether the bus is equipped, according to the technical permit, with walking places.
If the bus is not homologated, the passenger must be seated.
Student Agency long-distance buses have no standing places, company director Radim Jančura confirmed to Aktuálně.cz.
&quot;We have solved this with the ministry and, in principle, the movement of passengers is not allowed.
Finally this was withdrawn and we reached an agreement that passengers can go to the bathroom while the bus is running if they have a seat, &quot;he told us his position.
The stewardess does not know the law
&quot;There is no obvious legal interpretation of the role of the stewardess - no legal provision clarifies this role.
Not even any legal provision prohibits transport agents from performing any service.
The road transport law only knows the term Vehicle Inspector, whose rights and obligations are not defined &quot;, adds, less emphatically, the spokesman Hanzelka.
The director of the Department of Road Vehicle Traffic of the Ministry of Transport, Josef Pokorný, thinks on the contrary that the law sufficiently addresses this problem.
&quot;It depends on whether the bus has the approval allowed to have walking sites.
That&#39;s it, &quot;he says.
The buses are divided into urban, where there are places to stand and with a limited maximum speed, intercity with places to stand with a higher speed permit, and long-distance buses without places to go standing, with the highest permit. speed and with seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on the plane, says the expert
BESIP Transport Safety Expert Jaroslav Hořín does not see major problems regarding the movement of the steward on the bus.
&quot;During the development of the trip there is not much threat of danger, the situation can be compared to the service in airplanes.
Even here there is no guarantee that the turbulence will come and that the stewardess will hit her head. &quot;
&quot;However, if the bus stops suddenly the physical laws are obviously valid.
The same as on a city bus or on the tram.
The security of the stewardess must be solved by the internal regulations of the carrier, &quot;he says and also thinks that from the point of view of the law this problem is unsolved.
Jančura is prepared to cancel this service
Student Agency is the only carrier that offers the hostess service.
He employs two hundred on it.
The director, not even after the accident, considers that job risky.
&quot;However, the moment I get the impression that the stewardess position is risky, then I will abolish it.
Coffee and newspapers can be received by passengers as they enter.
It would even save expenses, &quot;he says.
In the interests of safety is the reason that Asiana lacks hostesses in its vehicles, according to Alexej Litvin, who runs a small line compared to SA.
&quot;We do not have hostesses, we are against them from the beginning.
Sooner or later this will end in a fatal accident, &quot;he told Týden.cz less than a year ago.
An enormous tragedy happened
In the accident on the line that connects Naples, a young hostess from Pilsen died, who had worked for the company for two years.
A Slovenian truck that probably veered from the parking lane blocking the bus. without using the turn signals.
Its driver tried in a quick maneuver to avoid it, however, he collided with the front right.
Jančura denies that the two places that are reserved for the hostess&#39;s rest were sold.
&quot;These sites cannot be reserved for long distance connections, they are blocked.&quot;
The company intends to sue the truck driver.
The agency is not going to wait for the verdict of the judgment on the compensation of the girl&#39;s family but expects the financial expenses also from the guilty party.
Law reform?
Not for now
The reform of the law could bring greater precision on the movement of the flight attendant on the bus in which thirty experts, members of a group from the Ministry of Transport, have been working for a year.
&quot;However, they have not reached any concrete conclusion.
They do not focus too much on buses, but rather on the point system, maximum speed on the motorway and the use of mobile phones while on the move, &quot;says expert Hořín.
&quot;The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of the hostesses something that significantly threatens the safety of passengers&quot;, ending the spokesman Hanzelka, that the control of security in buses is the responsibility of the police and the Security Office at work.
