Will Mr. Obama take a school like Sixth Street Prep as a model to be replicated by other schools with large Hispanic-English student populations?
The results achieved by this school should remove any doubt about the answer, but the idea of the politicians of his party on the issue of education (the Associations for National Education have long been advocates of bilingual education) and himself Constant support for bilingual education obscure the prediction of Mr Obama&#39;s response.
While immigrants must learn English, recently Mr Obama has trivialized the issue by letting people stop worrying about legislation that is only written in English
