Ms. Hurston is still remembered here as a vivacious eccentric who returned frequently after her family moved to Jacksonville, Florida.
Franklin Augusto, 77, is recalled that when Mrs. Hurston arrived in town, she did so without prior notice in a large Chevrolet, smoking and wearing pants in a city that still prides itself on dressing with dignity today.
