William Woodruff
Professor John Beckett writes:
in his William Woodruff sequel (25 September) he states that &quot;in 1946 he resumed his studies in economic history at Oxford and in 1950 he won a Houblon-Norman research fellowship ... at the same time he was studying for a bachelor&#39;s degree, one a master&#39;s degree and a doctorate. &quot;
