It should be noted that these measurements are for the version with the 1.4 engine, since the boot capacity of the Honda Jazz 1.2 is 379 liters.
Other improvements - in addition to exterior elements such as rear LEDs or the possibility of mounting the panoramic glass - is an improvement in access to the rear seats.
And it is that the doors that give access to the second row have an opening angle of 80 degrees, compared to the 67 degrees of the first Jazz.
Also new are the engines in this second generation Jazz.
At the beginning of its commercialization, this small model will have two gasoline engines of 1.2 and 1.4 liters.
Both mechanics incorporate i-VTEC technology that achieves lower consumption, emits less carbon dioxide, achieves excellent mechanical refinement and at the same time achieves high torque throughout the engine speed.
The first 1.2-liter mechanics gets a power of 90 horses at 6,000 revolutions with a maximum torque of 114 Nm. at 4,900 turns.
This engine - which in the previous Jazz reached 78 horses - has a consumption of 5.3 liters and emissions of 125 grams of CO2.
With respect to the previous engine, which in the previous generation achieved 83 horses, now it has 100.
This 100 horsepower Jazz 1.4 achieves a combined consumption of 5.4 liters and 128 grams of CO2.
