What did the Zuschlag &amp; Co. invoice factory produce?
Very soon, on October 8, the criminal proceedings will begin against János Zuschlag and his accomplices.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of committing fraud of significant damage, in a business manner, continuously and in an organized manner, in addition to other crimes, including the falsification of documents.
According to the Prosecutor&#39;s Office, they used the funds obtained in public tenders for their own purposes, justifying on many occasions the fulfillment of the tasks with false invoices.
The public funds and that of the municipalities - in total some 65 million HUF - stopped partly in the treasury of the Fiatal Baloldal organization and partly in the pockets of private individuals.
The method, which was also made known by the researchers, was to justify the collection of the funds obtained in the public tenders with false invoices behind which there was no real execution, the different associations never fulfilled their assumed obligations.
According to the prosecution, most of the invoices were false.
For this they obtained the checkbooks in the market of the District of Józsefváros and the circular stamps were manufactured in the city of Kiskunhalas.
And the question that in the name of which company the falsified invoice should be made was decided among others in that tour of the Upper Balaton Region where János Zuschlag sent István Lados.
The latter confessed that for this purpose he had to choose hostels and restaurants.
He requested an invoice for his consumptions and these served as a model to prepare the invoices that they presented, among others, in the competitions of the Ministry of Youth and Sports Affairs, the Ministry of Social and Labor Affairs, as well as the City Council of the Capital.
Most of these invoices were signed by István Lados and his accomplice András Őri, who according to our information rather wrote the necessary reports to obtain public subsidies.
During one of his &quot;field trips&quot; Lados chose a brewery.
According to two invoices issued in 2003 by Zuschlag and his accomplices, this gastronomic center provided food for a group of ninety people from the Biztos Pont Egyesület Association.
However - according to the manager of the center - so many people do not fit at the same time in that place.
Similarly, the invoice issued in the summer of 2002 for the Jobb Jövőért Foundation - later called Együtt to Harmadik Évezredért - was full of formal and contextual errors.
Well, a hostel in the town of Badacsonytomaj had only three rooms and more than ten people could not stay there in one night, however the bill included one hundred and thirty people.
But the manufacturers of fancy invoice also exaggerated when they pointed to the gastronomic center Pigal Kft. Because in the bookkeeping of the same - according to the information given to the Prosecutor&#39;s Office - there were no documents in the name of Jobb Jövőért and Hoppá.
Győző Farkas, the manager of said company, informed hvg.hu that when he was summoned by the prosecution and they showed him the invoices, he already knew that they were false documents.
&quot;On the stamp the name of our company and the NIF appeared in the wrong place.&quot;
He added: in addition to the formal problems, it did not agree that according to the bill one hundred people were accommodated, since they have only eleven rooms in which not so many people fit.
In addition, meals were also included in the bill, while the restaurant has not worked for a long time.
The enthusiastic invoice makers were also not informed that the chosen travel agency in Budapest exclusively organizes trips abroad, so that on the invoice for cash payment they foolishly indicated a trip within Hungary as a service, which also did not coincide with the agency invoice issuance practice.
In addition - as it became known during the investigation - VAT was also included in the document, despite the fact that trips outside the territory of the European Union were tax exempt.
Among other things, the VAT measure was also incorrect in the four documents issued by the Hotel Révfülöp Kft. For the Jobb Jövőért foundation, since the services of said company are not charged with 25 but only 15 percent VAT, In addition, the hotel employees only issued machine-made invoices, however the invoice was manual.
In addition, the &quot;dispatchers&quot; made other errors as well, as in the case of a company in which they put in the invoice as an activity carried out the road transport which - it was learned during the investigations of the prosecution - the company founded as a consultant does not perform investment.
Likewise, due to formal differences - inadequate format of the invoice, false stamp - it was learned that the invoices issued for Együtt to Harmadik Évezredért Alapítvány, for XXI, are false. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and for Biztos Pont.
As in the case of Ravenna Bt. Or the Kunfehértó Sports Camp, whose representatives denied having issued those invoices.
The forgers also did not pay attention to the fact that when the Fiatal Városért Egyesület group ate there (2001) the HIB Kft. Of Nyíregyháza was in the process of being liquidated, so the person in charge of the liquidation process - according to our information - denied having issued such a document.
Consciously issued invoices
Another group of manufacturers of false invoices are made up of those who were aware that they had to issue fictitious invoices.
The Esély Budapestért Alapítvány Foundation, at the request of Fiatal Baloldal - Ifjú Szocialisták, issued an invoice for a value of about four million HUF on behalf of the Együtt Foundation to Harmadik Évezredért.
The manager of the Collab Kft. - according to the indictment - was persuaded by one of the defendants, Ludovic Györfi, to issue fictitious invoices.
Similarly, Biogate Kft., Currently under liquidation, was collaborating with Zuschlag and his accomplices, which in 2003 provided invoices for an approximate value of five million HUF to the Jobb Jövőért Alapítvány foundation, the Atlasz Egyesület association and the Vörösfenyő association. Egyesület, with no real economic activity behind.
There was no movement of capital either, because later they canceled the invoices prepared but forgot to record this entity in their documents.
The next group of manufacturers of false invoices includes those who have some connection with the defendants.
For example, Ivan Kubatov was the defendant of the Ukrainian manager of Delta Trio SL with fictitious headquarters in Budapest, which dealt with the fuel and vehicle trade.
This company issued numerous invoices worth approximately HUF 18 million in October, November and December 2005 for the sale of computer media.
According to the data of the investigation, these invoices were bought by the Cash Investment Kft. Of Kiskunhalas, which since September 14, 2005 is under a liquidation process.
The manager of this company was a Romanian to whom Ivan Kubatov should have also dispatched the documents related to the company between 2002 and 2005.
We have information that Kubatov acknowledged during the investigation that he issued invoices for Atlasz, Hoppá and Együtt to Harmadik Évezredért Alapítvány on behalf of the company, collecting the amount himself.
Fa-Bani Jos Faipari Kft. And Jos-Investment Bt. Were founded by Romanian bricklayers at the express request of Iván Kubatov.
However, none of the companies functioned effectively because - according to the defendant - they did not receive work.
But he took advantage of these companies, since at the request of his accomplice the lawyer Zsolt Szente, who prepared the company&#39;s registration documents, they issued invoices on behalf of the companies for the organizations linked to Zuschlag: for the Atlasz and for the Y -Generated.
Kubatov on behalf of Cash Investment, Delta Trió, Fa-Bani Jos, Jos Investment and Linaxtrade gave a total of 15 invoices to different entities for a value of HUF 14.2 million.
The Prosecutor&#39;s Office considered that Kubatov received VAT and 10% of the amount of the invoices.
That man even took advantage of the Szi-Beri limited partnership to issue fictitious invoices used in the Biztos Pont contest.
The Y-Generáció and Szövetség a Modern Magyarországért presented a contest in January 2006 to Táncsics Mihály Alapítvány (TMA), a public utility entity of the Socialist Party.
From the contest they obtained 500 thousand HUF respectively, but they did not use the money for the purposes of the contest.
So that this is not discovered, they presented to the TMA five fictitious invoices received from the Works Team Kft.
These were the invoices found during the search of the office that Árpád Kemecsei had at the headquarters of the Ministry of Education.
Part of the defendants will probably relate in the trial - as they did in the Prosecutor&#39;s Office - the course of the falsification of the invoices.
The most interesting thing may be the confession of the main defendant János Zuschlag himself, if he decides to dismantle everything.
Well, his confessions so far have not been very detailed and although he repeatedly promised to talk about everything, this has not been done until now.
The question is: what is the interest in doing so? Well, perhaps in exchange for the return of most of the money - fifty million HUF - the Socialists reached an agreement with him so that Zusi assumes all the responsibilities.
Who, on the other hand, for these days could even be offended, since to alleviate his prison conditions he requested house arrest, but it was repeatedly denied.
While the numerous perpetrators of economic crimes of much higher value, who never returned the money, walk freely or at least can wait in their own home for the sentence, he has no possibility for that.
Overlapping Psychology: Why Do We Spend More Money?
Auction participants are prone to spending more money and overvaluing the product.
Neurologists and economists at New York University discovered the neurological-economic basis for this well-known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to the study in Science magazine, people do not want to lose in competitions such as eBay auctions, so they prefer to pay even an excessive price.
The scientists tried to establish the neurological scheme of this &quot;game&quot; by means of experimental auctions.
One of the groups of volunteers played the lottery, the other participated in an auction and meanwhile the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment were examined using the functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) system.
In both games the participants could win money, but during the auctions, where it is essential to bet more than the other, losing the game intensified the functioning of the complex called stratum located under the cerebral cortex.
This area of the brain, in addition to many other functions, plays a role in the &quot;reward&quot; mechanism of the nervous system.
Thus, according to the scientists, the increase in bets is explained as a prevention so as not to provoke an intense reaction from the stratum.
To support their theory, the economists of the scientific group also conducted a financial monitoring study.
In this experiment three groups bet against one person in different circumstances.
The control group was simply told the true value of the product in question, and its members bet.
Another group was also promised that if they win, they would receive an additional $ 15 prize.
On the other hand, the third group received exactly 15 dollars before the auction, but in case of losing the auction the members of the group lost even that money.
Thus, the only difference between the two groups was that for one the success was highlighted and for the other failure.
However, testing the neurologists&#39; hypothesis, the members of the group playing &quot;against failure&quot; were willing to bet even more than the members of the control group and the &quot;winning&quot; group.
&quot;These results cannot be deduced from any previously existing economic theory.
Well, those until now explained the phenomena of auctions only with the joy of winning and with the prevention of risks.
Only visual neurological methods helped resolve this contradiction between the two theories, so now we come to a third explanation &quot;- said Andrew Schotter, professor at the New York University School of Economics.
Hepatitis: When should you go to the doctor?
Around half a billion people worldwide suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, and in Hungary chronic liver disease is considered one of the leading causes of death.
The number of infected in this country is estimated at one hundred thousand, but only seven thousand receive treatment because many of the patients do not know that they are infected.
Hepatitis is the common name for different liver diseases caused by viruses.
The symptoms are very similar; Liver infection and jaundice are characteristic, but their pathogens and the diseases caused are very different.
Hepatitis viruses, depending on the pathogen, spread in two main ways: hepatitis A and E by food (for example with contaminated water or food), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and fluids bodily (sperm, vagina humor, saliva).
It is advisable for travelers to protect themselves by vaccination against viruses A and B, against C there are no vaccines.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two or three weeks after consuming the infected food, manifested by a poor general condition, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After that, jaundice appears on the skin and the whites of the eyes, the stool becomes light, the urine dark, and healing can take up to two - three weeks.
Annually one million people die in the world in cancer and liver cirrhosis caused by hepatitis B, the most serious forms of this disease.
The main reason for this is that according to estimates, only one in ten infected receives drug treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: without treatment it can cause liver cirrhosis and even cancer.
Most of those infected do not know they are sick because this pathological agent gradually destroys liver cells and many times the first symptoms only appear 20-30 years later.
Therefore, premature recognition, systematic medical control, is very important.
This disease is much more common in three groups: people who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug users and those who wear tattoos.
There are currently about 200 million people in the world with chronic hepatitis C.
As this disease can be discovered with a routine laboratory control as well, it is worth consulting with the family doctor when experiencing any unknown symptoms.
The disease can be cured if it is discovered in time, it is possible to exterminate the virus from the body, thus the contagion can be suppressed and cancer prevented.
September 30 is World Hepatitis Day, which was organized for the first time in 2004 by organizations representing the sick.
Its aim is to draw attention to the causes of chronic liver infections caused by viruses and the importance of their early recognition.
The governments of the Netherlands nationalize a part of the Fortis Bank.
The States of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization to the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis in the North American market: the three countries will support in total with 11.2 thousand million euros to this financial and insurance institution that also has business in Hungary.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held consultations at the highest level with the president of the European Central Bank and the head of economic competition at the European Commission.
Fortis Bank is the first to suffer the crisis in the Euro zone in the framework of the international financial crisis that has been occurring in several waves for more than a year, therefore the decisions taken with respect to the Bank, in a certain sense can be considered as precedents.
According to the decision adopted in the early hours of Sunday, the three states will buy approximately half (49 percent) of the property that the Bank owns in their area.
The Bank will certainly sell a part of its businesses, including mainly the activities - mainly insurance - bought last year from the Dutch ABN Amró.
Fortis shares began a sharp decline last week and by the second half of the week there were already significant signs of crisis in the institution.
However, analysts agree that with its 85,000 employees this Bank is too big to allow it to fail.
Shares in the company on Friday alone declined 12 percent, the lowest point in 14 years.
Since January the value of the shares has decreased by more than two-thirds.
Looking at current share prices, the total value of the group&#39;s capital on the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to company executives this is not real.
The Bank&#39;s management attributed the sharp fall in Fortis shares to the insecurities of the North American market in connection with the approval of the US $ 700 billion package plan.
On Monday the shares already showed a slight increase.
Filip Dierckx was appointed as the bank&#39;s new CEO on Friday.
The Bank also sought individual investors, but so far no one has made a specific offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured that investors did not have to worry, they will not lose their money.
So far there has been no panic among the Bank&#39;s clients, they have not invaded the bank offices to withdraw their money.
Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also bought leasing companies.
Does it hurt less to those who believe in God?
According to the result of a recent investigation, religious faith has a calming effect that also alleviated the death of the martyrs of Catholicism.
Scientists at the University of Oxford conducted an interesting experiment: they analyzed how religious belief influences human pain - reported the British newspaper Telegraph.
In the framework of this unique experiment, they applied electric shock to 12 Catholic believers and the same number of atheists, while all of them were looking at a painting of the Virgin Mary.
According to the results, the Catholic believers were able to exclude most of their pain.
Thanks to the human brain scanning technique, it was verified that Catholic believers were able to activate that part of their brain that is responsible for regulating pain.
This experiment is the first in a series of investigations in which scientists, philosophers and theologians from the different departments of the University also participate alongside academics.
The analysis occurred as follows; They attached a sparkling instrument to the patient&#39;s left hand, which applied the electric shock.
The researchers asked the experiment participants to fix their gaze on two paintings; the Virgin Mary, the work of Sassoferrato from the 17th century and the Lady with the Ermine by Leonardo da Vinci from the 15th century.
The researchers hoped that the Virgin Mary spectacle would provoke a certain religious mood among the faithful, while they chose Leonardo&#39;s oil because it was not too different from the other, and they thought it had a reassuring effect.
The patients spent half an hour in an MRI scanner, receiving in that period 20 electric shocks in four successive parts while observing the painting with a religious theme or the other.
Catholics affirmed that by looking at the Virgin Mary they felt &quot;safe&quot; as &quot;protected&quot; people, &quot;they calmed down and peace reigned in their hearts.&quot;
When looking at the painting with a religious theme, they felt 12 percent less pain than when they looked at Leonardo&#39;s work.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who also participated in the experiment, thinks that with any image that is so impressive, a similar effect can be achieved with atheists too, you just have to find the right image.
&quot;We should find the portrait of a person for whom they feel very positively, such as a mother or a father&quot; - said the psychologist.
Anglican Bishop Tom Wright celebrated the outcome of the investigation.
&quot;The exercise of faith should and in many cases really does change our personality&quot; - added Wright.
After these formidable results, only one question remains: what effect would it have on pain regulation if the faithful were shown the Madonna by Leonardo or another painter of his stature?
Would the vision of a high-quality Virgin Mary yield even better results?
You are what you say about yourself
On its tenth birthday, Google can affirm: it can be found both in people&#39;s pockets and in the sky above their heads; you know where they spent their vacations, which doctors they visit and what interests them.
But according to Eric Schmidt, one of the company&#39;s executives, this is still not enough.
On the other hand, the skeptics who make a parallel with the Orwellian vision do not see the essence of Web 2.0.
Eric Schmidt recently told the Financial Times newspaper that Google&#39;s primary goal is to gather as much personal data about its users as possible, and this is necessary in order to meet the original goals of Google&#39;s founders: &quot;Let&#39;s gather in one system! all the information in the world! &quot;.
According to the leader of Google, the company even after ten years of work that turned the world upside down is still in the initial phase of the effort to be able to process all the information.
To the question that what is going to happen in five years, Schmidt answered like this: I wish Google could answer questions such as &quot;What to do tomorrow?&quot; or &quot;What would be the best job for me?&quot; - however, the software will not be able to answer apparently so simple questions as long as there is not enough information from the users.
Not all Internet users are aware that while browsing the Internet, the searched keywords, the IP addresses and the pages to which they went at the end of the search are stored with precision.
Thanks, for example, to Personalized Search that debuted two years ago, users can store their own browsing history, they can return to consult what they were looking for before, what they opened and thanks to this history it will generate much more personalized searches -in this same logic, will base the Recommendations, in which the system will offer us products and services based on the previously defined and stored preferences.
What will happen if they take advantage of my data against myself, if they collect information about my activities? - ask those users who are concerned seeing Google&#39;s information monopoly.
In most cases rather the potential represented by the company is what can be fearful and not remorse, fear of punishment, longing for freedom or rebellion against power.
However, it is a confirmed fact that not only do they keep, but in justifiable cases they also transfer all the expressions sought to third parties, in these cases there is nothing that protects the personal rights of Internet users.
The most debated example in recent times was perhaps the coordinated action against Brazilian pedophiles, when Google gave the Brazilian government the information from its website, called Orkut, to identify pedophiles.
On the other hand, Internet users who care about people&#39;s rights, in the month of May were relieved when the company together with the EFF, organization for the defense of electronic rights, successfully demonstrated in court that it was right in its litigation with the FBI: according to the ruling, Google cannot be forced, through any of the points of the constitution, to supply any type of information secretly requested by the FBI.
(At the same time, the federal government managed to obtain, under the pretext of reinforcing the child protection law passed years ago, about fifty thousand Web addresses and some thousand search phrases, but without obtaining the search lists of individual users, nor Nor are the full lists of web pages and keywords for the last two months.)
Thus, the opinion about Google is quite contradictory: those who fear providing their personal data criticize it because they think that their privacy, their private life is harmed by starting to use Google services, and they rebel against it as well as against multinational companies of conservative image.
Meanwhile, the North American geek culture and its enthusiastic followers, Internet users and users from other countries, see in them the future generation, the &quot;vanguard corporation&quot;, not their rival, Microsoft, cataloged by its Windows as conqueror of the World , no matter how much they both fight for the same goal.
This can happen because Google, unlike Microsoft, does not ask users for any identification code or money for their applications, the code is open and the free program package is constantly updated and seems more youthful, more collaborative than practice. from the official software giant.
But it may also be because geeks see with precision the very problematic relationship between people&#39;s rights and the Internet, which was produced precisely by one of the most mentioned keywords in recent years: Web 2.0.
Web 2.0 is about collaboration, leaving intentional footprints behind us and taking advantage of available communication channels, and while the measures of these vary individually, the essence remains the same: to show ourselves.
A normal young person can have a profile on numerous collective pages, from Facebook to Xanga, and can even link them with other services, such as Twitter or last.fm that offers a list of their music habits, then they can include them in a monitoring system such as FriendFeed or Blip.fm, can also have a blog, in which the most recent photo galleries that are stored on Flickr or Picasa automatically appear.
We can know many cases from which it is clear that, for example, the girlfriend, when seeing the flow of photographs the next morning of mutual friends, finds out with whom her fraudulent boyfriend spent the night before or they can fire a company employee because He writes his honest opinion on his blog about the direction of the company: one thing is for sure, the definition of privacy has been completely revalued.
The &quot;online&quot; life of a person is what he shows of himself - this is the definition that hides behind the behavior of the youth of our days.
And whoever wants to hide something, or at least tries to avoid Google&#39;s monopoly, can do so (starting for example with Scroogle that uses the Google search system, but leaves no traces).
There are many people who do not want to register on the collective pages to avoid being found, but Google&#39;s &quot;on-line&quot; applications, from text writing software to image and news reading applications, can be replaced with alternative versions which do not connect with gigantic servers or prepare the most perfect profile possible about us.
Public opinion is almost openly waiting for the day when Google shows its true face.
The company with its current value of 156 billion dollars is worth more than IBM (140 billion dollars), Intel (124 billion dollars) or Coca-Cola (110 billion dollars), the surfaces of AdWords / AdSense advertising threatens the revenue of advertising agencies, while services that are being introduced more and more quickly cause serious headaches not only for Microsoft, but also for numerous other software developers.
Critical observers, however, will find the contradictions alarming as well: for example, the top management flatly rejected the employee&#39;s protest after doubling the price of the company&#39;s daycare, they considered the unlimited number of feeding of the employees too expensive, but All this is nothing compared to the fact that in 2006 Google gave in to pressure from the Chinese government and the company, according to the agreement, leaked all information that violated good morals and the interests of the Chinese regime.
One of the internal regulations of the company says that they will not announce any new service in advance, but only when it is ready to go, what is certain is that the foreseeable problems of the coming months and years will be able to stir the world: while Some believe that Google&#39;s book and magazine scanning and archiving project will acquire such dimensions that the company will soon be cited by the Supreme Court of the United States, others fear its Health system, because in it we can create our own health profile complete, with previous analyzes, with our doctors and our problems.
And the fact that Google is going to create a genetic database, may provide a good raw material for writers of science fiction works, Scroogled, a novel by the popular Cory Doctorow, describes in an Orwellian way that future, in which a man from only Google data can be described alarmingly well.
