The written version of the package was published before the opening of the Asian markets, that is, on Sunday before 8 p.m., according to Washington time (that is, before 2 a.m. on Monday, according to Central European time ), without causing a spectacular jump in the bags.
On the bill called the emergency law for economic stabilization of 2008, the North American Congress will vote first on Monday and then the Senate.
President George W. Bush on Saturday night consulted with Pelosi and then the White House also celebrated the news about the agreement.
We are pleased with the progress made overnight and highly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy - stated Tony Fratto, the White House spokesman.
The program is different from the Bush administration&#39;s original proposal to spend the entire $ 700 billion to buy shoddy credit fund securities.
Now only half of the 700 billion dollars can be spent, using 250 billion immediately after Congress votes, probably on Monday, of this sum the Ministry of Finance will buy securities of credit fund, poorly rated and the fate of another $ 100 billion depends on the president&#39;s decision.
This program will be controlled by a special body, in which the chairman of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The other half of the 700 billion dollars will be able to be spent after a new decision by Congress.
According to the law, the Ministry of Finance can apply a combined tactic: it can simultaneously buy bad loans, mortgages and credit fund securities, in addition to other &quot;poisonous&quot; type credits as well.
The purchase can be made at auctions or directly - informed competent persons from the ministry.
The law allows affected companies to participate in an insurance program where the financial portfolio guarantees the worrying elements, for which the companies will pay the amount corresponding to foreseeable damages.
Henry Paulson affirmed: the law ensures the necessary financial means in such a way that it can even reach 700 billion dollars to satisfy the urgent needs of the American financial system, be it the purchase of bad financial means, their insurance or the prevention of risks that could cause the collapse of some large financial institutions.
We do everything necessary to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it - he added.
On the other hand, the heads of the banks that are in distress and await the help of the State will be able to count on the official limitation of their indemnities, which the American slang simply calls a golden parachute.
Only in certain cases will payments be limited, in addition the limitations depend on the form of help from the finance ministry.
The limitation means that if the ministry buys at auction, an extra tax will be levied on the gold parachutes, unless the failed bank boss retires.
By buying bad loans outright, the government will intervene aggressively to ensure that boss payoffs are not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, the existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations refer only to the new contracts to stimulate participation in the program.
This is the first case in North American history that a legal limitation will be in force on the income of general directors - said the Democrat Barney Frank, chairman of the Congressional committee, responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares in the banks participating in the program, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, since ultimately they will even be able to obtain profits with the transaction as soon as the economy recovers and with it the bank.
According to the bill, in the next five years the president must present to Congress a proposal on how to return financial sector losses to taxpayers.
Of course, on both sides there were those who expressed reservations about the project.
This is not what the American citizens entrusted to us, that is, they are not protecting taxpayer dollars - declared the Republican Congressman from California, Darrell Issa.
His Ohio Democrat colleague Mary Kaptur said: the measures were urged by the very people who are responsible for the collapse of Wall Street.
