Some companies lately also prepare the results of laboratory tests and combining them with data on drug consumption obtain more accurate information on the patient&#39;s health status.
More and more companies have access to this data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those that provide health services.
The bill that provides the right to the authority to control specialized companies for the supply of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard recognizes that this is insufficient: therefore he developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that said person cannot deny his approval, because otherwise the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So the chickens, despite everything, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
